<HEAD>Bush Wins Idaho GOP Primary</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOISE, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vice President George Bush, who already has
a lock on the Republican presidential nomination, won Idaho's GOP
presidential primary Tuesday. The vice president's only opponent on
the ballot was Pat Robertson, who dropped out of the presidential
race earlier this month.
