<HEAD>Nuclear Opponents Destroy Garage At Construction Site</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WACKERSDORF, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nuclear power opponents threw a
fire bomb that destroyed a garage on the site of a proposed nuclear
waste recycling plant, police said. No injuries were reported.
   Police arrested 10 people after the fire bombing on Monday at
the construction site near the Bavarian village of Wackersdorf, 35
miles north of Regensburg. The garage, which housed construction
equipment, was destroyed by the resulting fire, police said.
   Earlier Monday, opponents of the planned nuclear facility
blocked a railroad line near Wackersdorf by placing tires and
pieces of wood on the tracks and setting the materials on fire,
police said.
   Train service on the line was delayed for about 3{ hours, police
said.
   On Sunday, 1,000 people protested the planned facility in a
rally next to the fence surrounding the site. The construction site
has been the scene of violent clashes between protesters and police
in the past.
