<1ST_LINE>u a AM-BowlingAlleyShooting     05-24 0247</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Bowling Alley Shooting,0253</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Gunman Kills One, Wounds One At Bowling Alley, Before Commiting
Suicide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman walked into a bowling alley
card room Monday and opened fire, killing one person and critically
wounding another before fleeing and then fatally wounding himself,
police said.
   Rodney Morrow, 34, of Sacramento, was carrying two guns when he
walked into the South Bowl shortly after 4 p.m. and fired two shots
without hitting anyone, authorities said.
   He then walked into the card room and shot an employee and
customer twice and then shot the employee again as he lay on the
floor, said police Sgt. Bob Burns.
   He said something to the effect of ``You are the one I want'' as
he shot the employee, Burns said.
   The gunman then walked out of the bowling alley.
   A police officer on patrol heard a radio report of the shooting,
spotted a man with a gun in his hand running along a busy street
and chased the gunman into a parking lot, Burns said.
   The gunman fired at the patrol car, knocking a large hole in the
windshield, and then shot himself in the head, Burns said.
   The police officer, James Kammerer, suffered minor cuts to his
head and right hand from flying glass, according to Burns.
   The bowling alley employee, who was killed, was identified as
Robert McGlone Jr., 30, of Sacramento. The customer, Carey Unruh,
was in critical condition at University Medical Center, police said.
</TEXT>
