<HEAD>Heads of Police, Air Force Fired in Dominican Republic</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Joaquin
Balaguer has fired the heads of the national police and air force.
   The action came Monday without any warning or official
explanation.
   Presidential decrees designated Col. Nelson Jose Morillo
Rodriguez as the new chief of police and Col. Fausto Miguel Cruz
Ramirez as head of the air force. Both were promoted to major
general.
   There was no explanation of why Gen. Fernando Aristides Sanchez
Aybar was dismissed as police chief or why Gen. Hector Miguel Roman
Torres was removed as head of the air force. Neither man was given
a new assignment.
   Morillo Rodriguez, the son of a former police chief, is the
fourth police chief appointed by Balaguer in his 22 months in
office. Sanchez Aybar was appointed March 3 during demonstrations
protesting the rising cost of living.
