<HEAD>Chinese Storm Wrecks 1,000 Homes</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A storm that killed 78 people in one province of
southeastern China has wrecked 1,000 homes elsewhere, it was
reported Tuesday.
   The official Xinhua News Agency said 42 bridges were also
damaged and 1,200 miles of highway flooded in Jiangxi province. No
casualties were reported.
   The rains, which began Friday, dumped up to a foot of water on
some parts of neighboring Fujian. Officials have reported 78 people
dead in the northern part of the province, more than 200 injured,
and more than 3,100 forced to flee their homes.
   Unusual weather has plagued much of China this month. Hailstorms
killed at least 24 people and injured more than 250 in coastal and
central China, and a tornado in Guangdong province in southeastern
China killed five people.
