<HEAD>House Republicans Say Bush Noriega Position Good</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Republican House members gave broad support
today to Vice President George Bush's quiet break with President
Reagan on the question of whether to negotiate with Panamanian
leader Manuel Antonio Noriega.
   The House Republican Conference, in a closed session with top
Bush campaign aides, also discussed recent national polls showing
the vice president trailing Gov. Michael Dukakis, his likely
Democratic opponent in the fall presidential election.
   Rep. Lynn Martin of Illinois, vice chairman of the conference,
said that ``almost to a person'' the GOP House members ``said they
were pleased about the separation on Noriega.''
   Bush indicated through aides last weekend that he opposed
negotiating with Noriega. The administration is trying to get the
