polls ``have him behind.''
   However, he said he told the House members ``we're in a very
artificial period, that period when Dukakis has been rolling along.
What you've got to do is get past this California primary before
people begin to focus on it.''
   ``We have bad polls,'' said Martin. ``If this were October, we'd
be suicidal. But this is May.''
   Martin said much of the discussion concerned ``how do we get the
George Bush we know apparent to the American people.''
   She said that because Dukakis was in a race against Jesse
Jackson ``he's been allowed to be defined as a moderate.''
