<1ST_LINE>r a PM-HikerDeath 1stLd-Writethru a0563 05-24 0316</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Hiker Death, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0563,0320</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police Find Suspect in Murder, Shooting</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES throughout with arrest of Carr, new details. No
Pickup.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>GETTYSBURG, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   State police today arrested a man
suspected of fatally shooting a hiker and wounding her companion,
culminating a two-day manhunt over rough mountainous terrain.
   About 50 police officers using dogs, horses and helicopters
began their search Monday morning for Stephen Roy Carr, 29, who
police believe lives in the mountains of the Cleversburg area at
the edge of the Michaux State Forest.
   Phil Carey of the Pennsylvania State Police said he did not know
where or when Carr had been arrested or whether he had been charged
in the case.
   State police, who had resumed their search this morning, planned
a news conference this afternoon in Harrisburg, Carey said.
   Sgt. John Straka of the state police in Gettysburg said Carr
matches the description by the surviving woman of a man the two
women had met earlier May 13, when the shooting occurred.
   ``We just want to talk to Mr. Carr,'' Straka said earlier. ``He
is considered a suspect and may be armed and dangerous. We know
that he has no fixed place of abode and that he does wander the
mountain area.''
   Cleversburg lies southwest of Harrisburg and northwest of
Gettysburg in southcentral Pennsylvania. It is about 4{ miles from
the shooting site _ a remote part of the state forest.
   Rebecca Wight, 29, of Blacksburg, Va., was shot and killed and
Claudia Brenner, 31, of Ithaca, N.Y., was shot in the face while
the two were camping in the state forest after a day of hiking the
Appalachian Trail.
   Ms. Brenner managed to walk about three miles to a road after
the shooting. She has been transferred from the Milton S. Hershey
Medical Center to another hospital for security reasons. She was in
stable condition, Straka said.
</TEXT>
