<HEAD>People In The News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oscar-winning filmmaker Oliver Stone is
making another Vietnam War movie, this one starring Tom Cruise.
   Stone will direct ``Born on the Fourth of July,'' based on the
life of Ron Kovic, who enlisted in the Army during the Vietnam War
and returned home paralyzed. Kovic then spoke against the war and
joined protesters he had once labeled traitors. He also wrote a
book about his experiences.
   The picture will begin filming in September.
   ``I think Oliver Stone is a terrific person to be making the
film _ the best person to do this story,'' said Kovic. ``The
message in the book and movie is listen, learn and never let it
happen again.''
   Stone's ``Platoon'' won four Academy Awards, including best
picture in 1986.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>PALM SPRINGS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Sonny Bono's mother and
stepfather have walked off their jobs at his restaurant after
allegedly being insulted by a new restaurant manager.
   ``It is a shock,'' said Bono's mother, Jean. ``But I am still
his mother at heart and I would rather not make him look like the
big bad wolf.''
   Bono's mother quit her hostess and public relations jobs the day
her husband, Tony Rose, quit as acting general manager of the
popular desert restaurant named Bono's.
   ``I was insulted by the new manager,'' Rose said.
   Bono, 53, confirmed that Rose left after a squabble with new
general manager, Dick House, but he declined to go into detail.
   ``I think it is something of a family matter and some things
have to stay in the family,'' said Bono, who became famous as half
the Sonny and Cher music team. ``I just wish he would have talked
to me rather than walking out.''
