<HEAD>Health Guru Jack LaLanne, At 73, Still Pushing Fitness</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MORRO BAY, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   After a half-century of touting
physical fitness, Jack LaLanne is still flexing his muscles without
a thought of retirement.
   ``Retirement! Geez. That's what Forest Lawn (mortuary) wants.
Retire and they get ya,'' the 73-year-old health guru said in a
recent interview from his coastal home 170 miles northwest of Los
Angeles.
   ``I don't care how long I live, I want to live while I'm
living,'' he said.
   Up at 5 a.m., LaLanne's daily ritual includes two hours of
pumping iron and stretching and an hour of exercise in the pool.
Then, he indulges in a blender concoction of nonfat milk, apple
juice, a banana and three packages of his own brand of
strawberry-flavored protein powder.
   With the frothy mixture, the one-time TV exercise personality
swallows about 100 vitamin and mineral supplements.
   But LaLanne isn't bent on force-feeding his philosophy.
   ``One of my best friends weighs about 300 pounds, drinks a quart
of booze a day and smokes like a fiend,'' he said. ``I'll light
someone's cigarettes for them. This bull about changing people _
you never change people. Accept 'em. accept 'em, accept 'em!''
