<HEAD>High-Mileage VW Crushed By Overturned Beer Truck</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Recasts 2nd graf to show 950,000 was approximate total sted
actual reading.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>RIVERSIDE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An elderly man says his Volkswagen had
lapped up nearly a million road miles before it was squashed like a
bug under an overturned beer truck.
   The 1966 Volkswagen had traveled about 950,000 miles based on
odometer readings before the accident Monday, owner Forrest Varing
said.
   ``Baby was about to make (1 million miles) but she flattened out
in the stretch,'' Varing, 67, said. He suffered only minor cuts in
the accident and the truck driver was unhurt.
   Both vehicles were traveling on a curved connecting ramp when
the truck, carrying a 22{-ton load of suds, overturned, crushing
the Volkswagen.
   ``It was the craziest accident I've ever seen and the beauty of
it was nobody got hurt,'' said California Highway Patrol Officer
John Anderson.
   Varing admitted not all the miles registered on the car's
odometer were driving miles, saying it was often towed behind other
cars during travels for his auto delivery business.
   Topping the Guinness Book of World Records car-mileage list is a
1957 Mercedes-Benz with 1,184,880 verified miles.
</TEXT>
