<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Obit-Guzzetti     05-24 0149</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Guzzetti,0154</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Argentine Ex-Foreign Minister Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Retired Vice Adm. Cesar Augusto
Guzzetti, who was foreign minister under Argentina's last military
regime, has died after a long illness, his family said Tuesday. He
was 62.
   Guzzetti, who died Monday, became foreign minister after a coup
on March 24, 1976 replaced the government of Isabel Peron with a
military junta that ruled through Argentina's ``dirty war'' years
until 1983.
   In May 1977, Guzzetti was seriously wounded during an attack by
leftist guerrillas who were seeking to overthrow the right-wing
military government. The guerrillas tried to kidnap Guzzetti while
he was visiting a doctor. They struck him on the head, badly
hurting him.
   Guzzetti resigned from office soon after the incident and went
to the United States for treatment, but remained debilitated the
rest of his life.
   He was buried in Buenos Aires with military honors.
</TEXT>
