<TEXT>
   President Reagan's decision to stop in Finland
for three days before the Moscow summit sent his hosts scurrying
for ways to entertain him in grand style. They even promised him an
audience with Santa Claus.
   St. Nick lives in Rovaniemi, a snowy town snuggled against the
