<1ST_LINE>d f BC-HongKong-Trade     05-24 0128</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Hong Kong-Trade,0133</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hong Kong's Trade Deficit Widens In April</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HONG KONG (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hong Kong's trade deficit was double in April
over what it was a year earlier, the Census and Statistics
Department reported Tuesday.
   It said the deficit was 3.390 billion Hong Kong dollars, or $434
million, last month, while it was 1.695 billion Hong Kong dollars
in April 1987.
   Domestic exports totaled 16.055 billion Hong Kong dollars, or
$2.05 billion, in April, up 10.4 percent from the same month last
year.
   Re-exported goods, which are assembled in Hong Kong from
components made elsewhere, rose 48.8 percent to 20.636 billion Hong
Kong dollars, or $2.64 billion.
   Imports totaled 40.081 billion Hong Kong dollars, or $5.13
billion, up 31.5 percent from April 1987, the department said.
</TEXT>
