<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Kleinwort-Fuji     05-24 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Kleinwort-Fuji,0132</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Japanese Bank Buying Stake In Kleinwort</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fuji Bank Ltd. has agreed to acquire 24.9 percent
of Kleinwort Benson Government Securities Inc., a Chicago-based
primary dealer in U.S. government securities, officials said Monday.
   Fuji will pay Kleinwort Benson's parent, London-based Kleinwort
Benson Lonsdale PLC, $14.5 million for the stake in addition to $25
million for all of the Chicago unit's subordinated debt, the
parties announced Monday.
   The deal, which is subject to Federal Reserve approval, would
give Fuji, the world's third-largest bank, a major foothold in the
U.S. securities market.
   Primary securities dealers trade directly with the Federal
Reserve Bank of New York. Such status is valuable because many
institutional investors will place orders only with firms that are
primary dealers.
</TEXT>
