<HEAD>London Shares Close Firmer; FT Index Up 21.6</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Updates with close.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices staged a broad-based rally in London
on Tuesday amid renewed takeover speculation.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index closed 21.6
points, or 1.2 percent, higher at 1782.9, slightly below its
highest level of the day.
   Trading volume was a moderate 459.6 million shares, compared
with Monday's 360.6 million shares.
   Wall Street failed to provide the direction for London equities
as in previous sessions and the London market appeared to be
trading on its own momemtum, dealers said.
   ``It's very encouraging to see London take the lead and perhaps
we're seeing the beginning of the decoupling from the U.S.
market,'' said Nicholas Knight, an equities analyst with James
Capel & Co. Ltd.
</TEXT>
